---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="The Cipher Archive" description="The Cipher Archive, revised with V17 data and built for static Netlify deployment.">
  <main class="wrap">
    <section class="hero grid hero-grid">
      <div>
        <div class="eyebrow">cipherarchive.org · V17 May 2026</div>
        <h1 class="title">The Cipher Archive<em>Community custody of working-class knowledge</em></h1>
        <p class="lead">
          Fifty-eight original concepts. A community-governed archive of working-class operational intelligence.
          A deployable Astro rebuild, static by default, with V17 concepts surfaced in clean semantic structure.
        </p>
        <p><a class="btn" href="#cipher">Explore the archive</a></p>
      </div>

      <aside class="card side">
        <div class="meta">
          <div>
            <div class="eyebrow">The project</div>
            <strong>Unnamed Intelligence</strong>
            <div class="small">A book and a living archive, funded and governed by the community it belongs to.</div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <div class="eyebrow">Funding progress</div>
            <strong>0 raised</strong>
            <div class="bar"></div>
            <div class="small">0 custodians · 25,000 goal</div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <div class="eyebrow">The framework</div>
            <div class="small">58 concepts · 5 clusters · 6 generative mechanisms</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </section>

    <section class="sections section" id="about">
      <div class="eyebrow">What this is</div>
      <h2>The intelligence does not need institutional permission to be real.</h2>
      <div class="grid text-cols">
        <p>The Cipher names working-class operational intelligence in a vocabulary built from inside the experience rather than above it. It is designed for semantic reading, accessible structure, and direct deployment on Netlify.</p>
        <p>The archive exists to hold named instances of that intelligence in community custody. The revised site keeps the project legible without the bulk of the original long-form HTML.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="sections section" id="cipher">
      <div class="eyebrow">The framework</div>
      <h2>The Cipher</h2>

      <div class="pillars">
        <article class="pill">
          <div class="eyebrow">01</div>
          <h3>Extraction Architectures</h3>
          <p>How systems extract labour and cultural production while producing ignorance.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="pill">
          <div class="eyebrow">02</div>
          <h3>Knowledge Systems</h3>
          <p>How working-class cognitive capability builds, transfers, and compounds.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="pill">
          <div class="eyebrow">03</div>
          <h3>Cognitive Architecture</h3>
          <p>How the practitioner reads, orbits, and orchestrates complexity under pressure.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="sections section" id="entries">
      <div class="eyebrow">Selected V17 entries</div>
      <h2>Entries updated from the V17 data</h2>

      <div class="entries">
        <details class="entry">
          <summary>
            <div class="mono small">01</div>
            <h3>Alpha-Induced Ignorance</h3>
            <p class="small">The ignorance isn't stupidity. It's engineered.</p>
          </summary>
          <div>
            <p class="deck">The engineered ignorance that results from systematically excluding working-class people from the institutions, professions, and knowledge systems that make decisions about their lives.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="entry">
          <summary>
            <div class="mono small">02</div>
            <h3>Architectural Agency</h3>
            <p class="small">Not a property an individual possesses. A condition a practitioner constitutes.</p>
          </summary>
          <div>
            <p class="deck">The form of agency produced by Atmospheric Conditioning that operates through presence, relational infrastructure, and distributed intelligence rather than through projected authority or performed identity.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="entry">
          <summary>
            <div class="mono small">03</div>
            <h3>Aspirational Asphyxiation</h3>
            <p class="small">The injunction to rise, delivered in the same breath that withdraws the conditions that would make rising possible.</p>
          </summary>
          <div>
            <p class="deck">The specific damage that occurs in the gap between formal invitation and substantive exclusion.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="entry">
          <summary>
            <div class="mono small">04</div>
            <h3>Atmospheric Conditioning</h3>
            <p class="small">The environment begins teaching before the practitioner knows they are being taught.</p>
          </summary>
          <div>
            <p class="deck">The developmental process through which the Cognitive Architecture loop is built.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="entry">
          <summary>
            <div class="mono small">05</div>
            <h3>Atmospheric Literacy GM</h3>
            <p class="small">Reading a room before anything has happened.</p>
          </summary>
          <div>
            <p class="deck">The systematic ability to read rooms, power dynamics, and escalation risk produced by sustained exposure to environments where misreading carried real cost.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="entry">
          <summary>
            <div class="mono small">06</div>
            <h3>Conditional Admission</h3>
            <p class="small">The admission is real. The condition is the violence.</p>
          </summary>
          <div>
            <p class="deck">Formally admitted on the condition that working-class people perform assimilation and suppress the intelligence they arrived with.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="entry">
          <summary>
            <div class="mono small">07</div>
            <h3>Compound Precarity</h3>
            <p class="small">Not poverty plus insecurity.</p>
          </summary>
          <div>
            <p class="deck">The specific architecture of simultaneous multiple precarity, in which addressing one domain costs resource from another.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="entry">
          <summary>
            <div class="mono small">08</div>
            <h3>Cognitive Starvation</h3>
            <p class="small">The loop cannot run.</p>
          </summary>
          <div>
            <p class="deck">The deliberate or structural design of work and environments to prevent the development of critical intelligence.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="entry">
          <summary>
            <div class="mono small">09</div>
            <h3>SMDO — Simultaneous Multi-Domain Orchestration</h3>
            <p class="small">The room is never only one thing at once.</p>
          </summary>
          <div>
            <p class="deck">The capacity to hold multiple operational domains open simultaneously under genuine pressure.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="entry">
          <summary>
            <div class="mono small">10</div>
            <h3>Tactical Multiplicity</h3>
            <p class="small">Simultaneous holding of multiple authentic identity registers without collapsing any.</p>
          </summary>
          <div>
            <p class="deck">The working-class cognitive architecture training ground from which SMDO develops.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="sections section" id="archive">
      <div class="eyebrow">The archive</div>
      <h2>This archive grows through knowledge, not promotion.</h2>
      <p>
        For a full production version, the remaining V17 entries can be added as additional details blocks or generated from a data file.
        This starter keeps the site static, semantic, and easy to deploy to Netlify.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="sections section" id="back">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="eyebrow">Back the book</div>
        <h2>Fund the book. Build the archive. Own the vocabulary.</h2>
        <p class="small">
          This Astro version is intentionally minimal: no client-side framework, no dynamic rendering, just clean content structure and deployable static output.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer class="footer wrap">
    <p>The Cipher Archive · 2026 · Rob Dawson · SPACE CIC</p>
  </footer>
</Layout>
